{
  "text": "The latest and largest study of the Munich Cancer Registry has demonstrated the relevance of combined RP and PLND. Among 13805 patients 938 (10.2%) had LN+ status. 688 LNpositive patients underwent RP and 250 LN-positive patients did not. Patients who underwent both RP and PLND showed 2 Advances in Urology a relative survival (RS) rate of 86.2% after 10-year follow-up, while patients who only underwent PLND had a RS of only 40.5%. In other words, patients who also underwent RP had a twice as high chance of RS compared to those that did not [CITATION_1] .",
